<br>
I consider myself an expert on the matter... Unfortunately, I wasted many hours trying to figure it out..tried all known theories and made up my own. Like killing the putrids in numerical order (when you offer the skellies a coin from far it will say &quot;you are too far away from putrid skelly_02 to trade, for example)  <br>
<br>
Finally I proved the &quot;ph every 3hrs 20min&quot; theory correct<br>
<br>
and it is possible to get both pieces in one day: <br>
<br>
a) Kill ph<br>
b) wait 3hrs 20min  (RL time) when either Grimrot pops or another PH (This is random so he may pop on the first attempt)<br>
c) kill the next ph so that in 3hrs and 20min (RL time)   the other Grimrot will pop or another ph (This is random so the other may pop on this next attempt)<br>
<br>
with luck one day is possible<br>
<br>
In my experience, undead version pops at night (game time) and live version pops at day (game time)<br>
<br>
