<br>
1)  The rumor about killing the PH at 3am eq time and 3pm eqtime (when he is up) to get Grimrot to spawn the next cycle may very well be unsubstantiated......but it work for me on the live version.  The undead version - I just happened to be walking by while he was up.<br>
<br>
For those of you that DON't Know....there is a rumor that says...kill the place holder at 3am (night) eq time to get LIVE version...and 3pm (day) eq time to get the undead version.<br>
<br>
2) Faction needed to get & complete the quest is ALLY w/ the Temple of Life.<br>
<br>
3) If you have friends with you...level 35 should be sufficient to take down the undead version....don't forget, this guy is a Shadowknight...and has a pet.  The live version....well I was with 2 paladin friends who were both level 50-ish when I completed this (which was when i was level 34) and they took down the live version but were both left with about half a bar of life.  So at level 35....I would expect a WHOLE group would be needed....or call in some high level friends (2 or 3) and you should be fine.<br>
<br>
4) The biggest pain about this camp is the length of the spawn time.....2 1/2 eq days for the spawn.  Which works out to what....2 1/2 - 3 hours REAL TIME for each spawn from the time of killing the PH.  I remember when i got the undead version on PURE LUCK zoning into S.K. to make a run to Rathe Mountains that he happened to be up...so I got interested in doing the quest.  Well it was about 4-6 weeks later that i actually got the other half of the drop from the LIVE version.  Now I wasn't camping him constantly, but I do remember doing the camp through a couple of spawns on more than one occassion and beginning to think I was NUTS!  Well I happened by a couple of Paladins who were doing it...both needing the UNDEAD version's piece.  Well I asked if I could sit with them and help...they said sure.  Low and behold the next spawn - which was about an hour into me being there - was the LIVE version.  I cheered and assisted in the kill.  Both of them looked at me...smiled...and told me to go ahead and loot since they both had that piece. I could not have been happier and luckier !<br>
